snippet.textDisplay:
Notice how yoongi blends into the crowd with the others at
2:13
And then after says "yeah I'm you, you are me, now do you know"

Is he referring to the pressure of being a famous idol?
Like if I'm in his shoes then I'd know how he feels

And also yoongi says "don't let me shine, don't let me down, dont let me fly"

"Now I'm afraid"

He even says something about being afraid and that flying high is terrifying, (probably talking about how scary it is to be so well known and a so legendary and amazing idol 😊)

He also mentions that no one told him how alone he'd be and somewhere in the beginning he said "I wondered every day how far I'd go"

It all points to the bad stuff about being so high and worldwide known

And don't forget, how many times he mentions the shadows. Grows as intense as the light, how scary it is, how it makes him hate the fact that he keeps rising up

(Dont get me wrong I'm not telling you to stop stan him)

His talking about his view and the flaws of being who he is right now

This song definitely shows me a different side of being famous that I never was aware off (or realised the importance of)

I'm so amazed it's just so fascinating how well he portrayed his message with this song

This man is legendary

snippet.textDisplay: BTS has given so much to korea and people worldwide, they wanted to be musicians, yet they have become something much bigger. Ofcourse they are thankful, but they are also paying a huge price for all this. They have no right over themselves. They are what ppl want them to be. They overwork and are always under tons of pressure. Life is a race for them. They are giving up their youth for all this. Because of that at times I wonder what are we even giving them in return?  Money, fame never bring you peace. They only bring another test. You can be drowned in pleasure and have your soul yearning for peace.
